Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Finely chop one half of the onion. Cut the other half into wedges. Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked from stalks) and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pop the @diced butternut squash{300%g} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{1}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden and cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}. Halfway through cooking, add the red onion wedges and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and turn to coat, adding a little more oil if you need to. Turn everything to coat evenly and roast for the remaining time.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #saucepan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the finely chopped red onion and cook, stirring frequently, until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once soft, add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and cook, stirring, until evaporated, ~{1%minute}. Pour the @water{240%ml} for the bulgur wheat into the saucepan and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @vegetable stock powder{1}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Quarter the @pomegranate{1/2}. Holding the pomegranate pieces over a #bowl{} of water, scoop out the seeds into the bowl of water.

> TIP: Use a fork to do this, it helps to release the seeds.

Scoop out the seeds and set aside. Discard the white pith.

Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g}(crumbled). Pop half of the mint into a #small bowl{} with a squeeze of lemon juice and the olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and mix together.

Once the vegetables are roasted add them into the bulgur with any cooking juices. Add the lemon zest and remaining mint and carefully combine everything together. Taste and season with salt and pepper if you think it needs it. Carefully stir everything together then divide between plates. Top with the crumbled feta, spoon over the drizzle and finish with the pomegranate seeds. Enjoy!